fix(#365): translate CreateTableError into a rejected SchemaAck in the destination handshake

The DDL builder wraps a missing type-map write rule as CreateTableError
(keeping the original only as __cause__), so the handshake's dedicated
type-map clause never matched by type and the error escaped to the
stream's outer except, failing the whole StreamRecords RPC instead of
producing the documented SchemaAck(accepted=False, "type-map: ...").

Add CreateTableError to the deterministic catch (build-time only on this
path: no columns, PK missing from the column list, missing type-map
write rule; DDL execution failures raise raw driver errors and still
fail the RPC). Preserve the "type-map: " prefix when __cause__ is a
type-map error so the engine log keeps the same signal either way. The
worker hop runs the same servicer, so the proxy now receives the real
rejection reason too.

